{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770322198,"nonce":"XMsIrC5MUBsCECHR5v/1iJFTSXE=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87oqOL-","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/175","origin":"github"},"title":"Update agent instructions to include refactoring and doc update steps","message":"## Problem\n\nAgent instructions in `.github/copilot-instructions.md` don't emphasize:\n- Refactoring before adding features\n- Documentation as part of implementation (not afterthought)\n- Legacy code removal when modernizing\n\nSession friction (issue #170):\n1. Initial PR had code duplication\n2. Legacy code not removed\n3. Docs updated only after being asked\n\n## Solution\n\nUpdate agent instructions to make cleanup and documentation first-class steps.\n\n## Implementation\n\nAdd to `.github/copilot-instructions.md`:\n\n```markdown\n## Code Modification Workflow\n\nWhen modifying existing scripts:\n\n1. **Analyze First**\n   - Check for code duplication opportunities\n   - Identify legacy code paths that can be removed\n   - Review what documentation will be affected\n\n2. **Implement**\n   - Extract functions to avoid duplication\n   - Remove (don't just bypass) legacy code\n   - Update inline comments\n\n3. **Document** (same PR, not separate)\n   - Update script header comments\n   - Update .agent/scripts/README.md\n   - Update user-facing docs (README.md, QUICKSTART.md)\n   - Check for stale references in other docs\n\n4. **Verify**\n   - Run: \\`bash -n script.sh\\`\n   - Test happy path\n   - Ensure docs match actual behavior\n```\n\nReference checklist from issue #173.\n\n## Benefits\n\n- Agents follow systematic process\n- Higher quality initial PRs\n- Less back-and-forth in reviews\n- Documentation stays current","files":null}]}